      <ol>
        <li>Handle queries from volunteers (although we hope most questions will go to the mailing list or discussion group). If in doubt then refer to one of the Executive, and we will try to invent an answer!</li>
        <li>Answer questions from Researchers and check and make corrections to transcriptions if necessary.</li>
        <li>Liaise with existing sources of transcriptions (e.g. the relevant County Record Office / Archive). Where there is no existing relationship, support the SWAT Team in obtaining permission, if requested.</li>
        <li>Set up Church and Register Type records in advance of the start of transcribing.</li>
        <li>Ensure that transcribers use the standard names for Place, Church and Register Type.</li>
        <li>Keep tabs on who is doing what, which parishes have been done, and what is available to be transcribed. You will need to keep your own record of this at present.</li>
        <li>Arrange for images to be transcribed to be loaded onto the Image Server and then ask for these to be allocated to transcribers as they need them.</li>
        <li>Gather data files from volunteers and upload them if they are not uploaded direct. If data files are not in our standard format, ready to be incorporated into the database, pass them to one of the data editing volunteers.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="push-half--bottom">Other responsibilities include:</p>
      <ol>    
        <li>Establish a syndicate discussion group and/or mailing list to use for passing information to your team and answering their questions.</li>
        <li>Correspond with volunteers providing data for your syndicate.</li>
        <li>If you wish, recruit and train volunteers to transcribe registers, or pass them to the Training Coordinator.</li>   
        <li>Identify and solicit contributions of existing transcriptions.</li>
        <li>Find work to be transcribed. This can be from many sources so contact the [ Data Manager ] for help.</li>      
        <li>Work with other Coordinators through the [Coordinators mailing list] and discussion group and keep the Country Coordinators informed of country-wide issues.</li>
        <li>Inform the [Executive] of improvements that should be made to FreeREG.</li>
        <li>Inform the [Web Managers] of problems with the website.</li>
        <li>Inform the [Executive] of their physical mailing address.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <h3>Getting started</h3>
    <p>Enquiries from volunteers will start to come directly to you, but any that we receive will be forwarded to you.</p>
    <p>Please familiarise yourself with the the various pages in the Information for Transcribers section so that you can point transcribers to the relevant pages.</p>
